What you need to know:

Six thousand five hundred and seventeen girls are ready to sit for KCPE compared to 6,332 boys while 5,764 girls are prepared to do KCSE compared to 5,217 boys.Tharaka Nithi County Director of Education, Ms Bridget Wambua said that for the private candidates, 40 females will do the national examinations compared to 36 males.